description.gco:CharacterString: Using the implementation guidelines, GIS staff at the Bureau of Land Management's (BLM) Eastern States (ES) office cross-walk and clean up their data to comply with the standardized national dataset. The BLM field and/or state offices submit the data to the National Operations Center (NOC), where it is compiled to produce seamless national datasets.

description.gco:CharacterString: This official BLM Data Management handbook contains information about how data is administered, managed, and tracked. The information this resource contains also pertains to geospatial data.
